"Moatar F., Gailhard J.","Water temperature behaviour in the River Loire since 1976 and 1881",2006,"Comptes Rendus - Geoscience","338","5",,"319","328",,,10.1016/j.crte.2006.02.011,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33646721734&partnerID=40&md5=a9fabc432d1c703e98abccb69a8b7161","Laboratoire de géologie des environnements aquatiques continentaux (GéEAC), UPRES EA 2100, université François-Rabelais, parc de Grandmont, 37200 Tours, France; Électricité de France, division technique générale, 21, av. de l'Europe, 38040 Grenoble cedex 9, France","Moatar, F., Laboratoire de géologie des environnements aquatiques continentaux (GéEAC), UPRES EA 2100, université François-Rabelais, parc de Grandmont, 37200 Tours, France; Gailhard, J., Électricité de France, division technique générale, 21, av. de l'Europe, 38040 Grenoble cedex 9, France","Analysis of monthly mean river temperatures, recorded on an hourly basis in the middle reaches of the Loire since 1976, allows reconstruction by multiple linear regression of the annual, spring and summer water temperatures from equivalent information on air temperatures and river discharge. Since 1881, the average annual and summer temperatures of the Loire have risen by approximately 0.8 °C, this increase accelerating since the late 1980s due to the rise in air temperature and also to lower discharge rates. In addition, the thermal regime in the Orleans to Blois reach is considerably affected by the inflow of groundwater from the Calcaires de Beauce aquifer, as shown by the summer energy balance. To cite this article: F. Moatar, J. Gailhard, C. R. Geoscience 338 (2006). © 2006 Académie des sciences.","Global warming; Influence of the Beauce aquifer; Multiple regression analysis; River Loire; Water temperature","global warming; multiple regression; river discharge; river water; water temperature; Eurasia; Europe; France; Loire River; Western Europe",,,,,,"Albéric, P., River backflooding into a karst resurgence (Loiret, France) (2004) J. Hydrol., 286, pp. 194-202; Albéric, P., Lepiller, M., Oxydation de la matière organique dans un système hydrologique karstique alimenté par des pertes fluviales (Loiret, France) (1998) Water Res., 32, pp. 2051-2064; Chapra, S., (1997) Surface Water-Quality Modeling, Civil Engineering Series, , McGraw-Hill International Editions; Daufresne, O., Roger, M.C., Capra, H., Lamouroux, N., Long-term changes within the invertebrate and fish communities of the Upper Rhône River: effects of climatic factors (2003) Global Change Biol., 10, pp. 124-140; Eaton, J.G., Scheller, R.M., Effects of climate warming on fish thermal habitat in streams of the United States (1996) Limnol. Oceanogr., 41 (5), pp. 1109-1115; Laubier, L., Changement et vulnérabilité des peuplements marins côtiers (2003) C. R. Geoscience, 335, pp. 561-568; Moatar, F., Miquel, J., Poirel, A., A quality-control method for physical and chemical monitoring data. Application to dissolved oxygen levels in the River Loire (France) (2001) J. Hydrol., 252, pp. 25-36; Moisselin, J.-M., Schneider, M., Canellas, C., Mestre, O., Les changements climatiques en France au XXe siècle. Etude des séries homogénéisées de données de température et de précipitations (2002) La Météorologie, 38, pp. 45-56; Mohseni, O., Stefan, H.G., Erickson, T.R., A non-linear regression model for weekly stream temperatures (1998) Water Resour. Res., 34 (10), pp. 2685-2692; Mohseni, O., Stefan, H.G., Stream temperature/air temperature relationship: a physical interpretation (1999) J. Hydrol., 218, pp. 128-141; Planton, S., À l'échelle des continents : le regard des modèles (2003) C. R. Geoscience, 335, pp. 535-543; Webb, B.W., Trends in stream and river temperature (1996) Hydrol. Processes, 10, pp. 205-226; Webb, B.W., Nobilis, F., Water temperature behaviour in the River Danube during the twentieth century (1994) Hydrobiologia, 291, pp. 105-113","Moatar, F.; Laboratoire de géologie des environnements aquatiques continentaux (GéEAC), UPR